    </li>
    <li>Restart OpenCode</li>
  </ol>

  <h3 id="editor-openclaw">OpenClaw</h3>
  <p>OpenClaw uses skills instead of MCP. The shell hook gives you automatic compression:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><code>lean-ctx init --global</code> — installs shell aliases</li>
    <li>Restart your shell</li>
    <li>Every <code>exec</code> call in OpenClaw is now automatically compressed</li>
  </ol>
  <p>For deeper integration, install the <a href="https://github.com/yvgude/lean-ctx/tree/main/skills/lean-ctx">LeanCTX skill</a> into <code>~/.openclaw/skills/lean-ctx/</code>.</p>

  <h3 id="editor-pi">Pi Coding Agent</h3>
  <p>Pi uses an extension-based system. The <code>pi-lean-ctx</code> package overrides Pi's built-in <code>bash</code>, <code>read</code>, <code>grep</code>, <code>find</code>, and <code>ls</code> tools to route them through lean-ctx.</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Install lean-ctx (if not already installed):
      <pre><code>cargo install lean-ctx</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li>Install the Pi extension:
      <pre><code>pi install pi-lean-ctx</code></pre>
      <p>Or use the lean-ctx installer:</p>
      <pre><code>lean-ctx init --agent pi</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li>All tools are now automatically routed through lean-ctx — no manual prefixing needed</li>
    <li>Verify with the <code>/lean-ctx</code> slash command inside Pi</li>
  </ol>
  <p>
    <strong>Smart reads:</strong> The extension automatically selects the optimal read mode based on file type and size
    (full for small files, map for medium code files, signatures for large code files).
  </p>

  <h3 id="editor-other">Other Editors with MCP Support</h3>
  <p>Any editor that supports the <a href="https://modelcontextprotocol.io">Model Context Protocol</a> can use lean-ctx. The general pattern:</p>
  <pre><code>{`{
  "mcpServers": {
    "lean-ctx": {
      "command": "lean-ctx"
    }
  }
}`}</code></pre>
  <p>Key points:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>The <code>command</code> must point to the lean-ctx binary (use full path if the short name doesn't work)</li>
    <li>No <code>args</code> needed — lean-ctx auto-detects MCP mode when invoked without arguments</li>
    <li>No <code>env</code> or <code>port</code> config needed — lean-ctx uses stdio transport</li>
    <li>Always restart the editor after changing MCP config</li>
  </ul>

  </details>

  <h2 id="monitor">Monitor Savings</h2>
  <pre><code># Terminal dashboard (colors, bars, sparklines)
lean-ctx gain

