  <h2 id="lctx">Multi-Agent Launcher (lctx)</h2>
  <p>
    The <code>lctx</code> command auto-detects your AI agent, builds the project graph, and launches with lean-ctx pre-configured:
  </p>
  <pre><code># Auto-detect and launch
lctx

# Launch a specific agent
lctx cursor
lctx claude
lctx codex
lctx gemini

# List supported agents
lctx --list</code></pre>
  <p>Supported agents: Cursor, Claude Code, OpenAI Codex, Google Gemini, Windsurf, Cline. The launcher:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Finds your project root (nearest <code>.git</code> directory)</li>
    <li>Builds or updates the persistent project graph (<code>ctx_graph build</code>)</li>
    <li>Launches the agent with lean-ctx MCP server configured</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Install the launcher script:</p>
  <pre><code># Copy to your PATH
sudo cp bin/lctx /usr/local/bin/
# Or symlink
sudo ln -sf $(pwd)/bin/lctx /usr/local/bin/lctx</code></pre>

  <h2 id="update">Updating</h2>
  <p>The fastest way to update is the built-in self-update:</p>
  <pre><code>lean-ctx update</code></pre>
  <p>This downloads the latest release from GitHub, verifies the binary, and replaces the current installation. Works on all platforms.</p>
  <p>Alternatively, use the same method you used to install:</p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Method</th><th>Command</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Homebrew</td><td><code>brew update && brew upgrade lean-ctx</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Cargo</td><td><code>cargo install lean-ctx</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>npm</td><td><code>npm update -g lean-ctx-bin</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>AUR</td><td><code>yay -Syu lean-ctx</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>install.sh</td><td>Re-run <code>curl -fsSL https://leanctx.com/install.sh | sh</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Binary</td><td>Download latest from <a href="https://github.com/yvgude/lean-ctx/releases/latest">GitHub Releases</a></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p><strong>After updating, always re-run:</strong></p>
  <pre><code>lean-ctx setup           # re-configures shell + editors
source ~/.zshrc          # restart shell</code></pre>

  <h2 id="uninstall">Uninstalling</h2>

  <p>
    Starting with v2.8.0, lean-ctx includes a built-in uninstall command that removes all configuration:
  </p>

  <pre><code>lean-ctx uninstall</code></pre>

  <p>This command removes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Shell hook</strong> — removes the lean-ctx block from <code>~/.zshrc</code>, <code>~/.bashrc</code>, <code>~/.config/fish/config.fish</code>, or your PowerShell profile</li>
    <li><strong>MCP configurations</strong> — removes the <code>lean-ctx</code> entry from Cursor, Claude Code, Windsurf, Gemini CLI, Antigravity, Codex CLI, VS Code, and OpenCode</li>
    <li><strong>Data directory</strong> — removes <code>~/.lean-ctx/</code> (stats, sessions, cache, config)</li>
  </ul>

  <p>After running the command, remove the binary itself:</p>

  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Installed via</th><th>Remove command</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Cargo</td><td><code>cargo uninstall lean-ctx</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Homebrew</td><td><code>brew uninstall lean-ctx</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>AUR</td><td><code>yay -R lean-ctx</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Manual binary</td><td><code>rm $(which lean-ctx)</code></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>Then restart your terminal. All lean-ctx compression aliases and MCP tools will be gone.</p>

  <h2 id="troubleshooting">Troubleshooting</h2>

  <h3>lean-ctx: command not found</h3>
  <p>The binary isn't in your PATH. Check where it was installed:</p>
  <pre><code># Cargo installs here:
ls ~/.cargo/bin/lean-ctx

# Homebrew installs here (macOS):
ls /opt/homebrew/bin/lean-ctx

# Manual installs — wherever you placed it:
ls /usr/local/bin/lean-ctx</code></pre>
  <p>Add the correct directory to your PATH in your shell profile.</p>

  <h3>MCP tools don't appear in editor</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Make sure you restarted the editor completely after adding the MCP config</li>
    <li>Check that <code>lean-ctx --version</code> works from the terminal the editor uses</li>
    <li>Try using the <strong>full path</strong> to the binary in the MCP config (e.g. <code>/Users/you/.cargo/bin/lean-ctx</code>)</li>
    <li>Run <code>lean-ctx doctor</code> to diagnose PATH and configuration issues</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Shell commands hang or recurse</h3>
  <p>If <code>cargo test</code> or other commands hang after installing lean-ctx aliases, prefix with <code>LEAN_CTX_ACTIVE=1</code> to bypass the alias:</p>
  <pre><code>LEAN_CTX_ACTIVE=1 cargo test</code></pre>
  <p>This is only needed when lean-ctx itself runs the same command internally (e.g. during builds or tests).</p>

  <h3>macOS: "cannot be opened because the developer cannot be verified"</h3>
  <pre><code>xattr -d com.apple.quarantine $(which lean-ctx)</code></pre>

  <h3>Windows: lean-ctx.exe not recognized</h3>
  <p>Make sure the folder containing <code>lean-ctx.exe</code> is in your PATH. Open a <strong>new</strong> terminal after changing PATH — existing terminals don't pick up changes.</p>

